WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:17.000
<font color=green size=18> <i> Subtitle Collected By : Mostofa Kamal </i> <i>
Mostofa_Kamal_86@yahoo.com </i>
<i>www.Facebook.com/Mostofa.kamal.86</i>

2
00:00:25.270 --> 00:00:27.238
[CHITTERING]

3
00:00:35.613 --> 00:00:37.604
[VOICES WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

4
00:00:44.289 --> 00:00:48.248
SCRIMGEOUR:
These are dark times. there is no denying.

5
00:00:48.860 --> 00:00:54.492
Our world has. perhaps.
faced no greater threat than it does today.

6
00:00:55.466 --> 00:00:59.425
But I say this to our citizenry:

7
00:00:59.604 --> 00:01:03.506
We. ever your servants...

8
00:01:03.675 --> 00:01:06.337
...will continue to defend your liberty...

9
00:01:06.511 --> 00:01:10.845
...and repel the forces
that seek to take it from you.

10
00:01:12.050 --> 00:01:17.317
Your Ministry remains...

11
00:01:17.855 --> 00:01:19.823
...strong.

12
00:01:22.994 --> 00:01:24.985
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

13
00:01:25.163 --> 00:01:27.154
[RAINDROPS PATTERING]

14
00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:35.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

15
00:01:37.175 --> 00:01:39.370
MRS. GRANGER:
Hermione. Tea's ready. darling.

16
00:01:39.544 --> 00:01:41.478
Coming. Mom.

17
00:01:45.416 --> 00:01:47.316
VERNON:
Come on. Dudley. hurry up.

18
00:01:47.485 --> 00:01:50.511
DUDLEY: I still don't understand
why we have to leave.

19
00:01:50.688 --> 00:01:55.455
VERNON: Because. unh.
it's not safe for us here anymore.

20
00:02:10.842 --> 00:02:15.211
Ron. tell your father
supper's nearly ready.

21
00:02:20.218 --> 00:02:21.947
MR. GRANGER:
Is this in Australia?

22
00:02:22.120 --> 00:02:24.088
MRS. GRANGER:
Looks wonderful. doesn't it?

23
00:02:24.255 --> 00:02:29.124
<i>MAN [ON TV]: Three and a half thousand
kilometers along Australia's east coast.

24
00:02:30.428 --> 00:02:31.952
<i>Obliviate.

25
00:04:39.090 --> 00:04:41.081
[CHATTERING]

26
00:04:46.297 --> 00:04:47.958
VOLDEMORT:
Severus.

27
00:04:48.132 --> 00:04:51.499
I was beginning to worry
you had lost your way.

28
00:04:51.669 --> 00:04:55.127
Come. we've saved you a seat.

29
00:04:59.577 --> 00:05:00.908
You bring news. I trust?

30
00:05:01.078 --> 00:05:04.741
It will happen Saturday next. at nightfall.

31
00:05:04.916 --> 00:05:07.282
YAXLEY:
I've heard differently. my Lord.

32
00:05:07.451 --> 00:05:10.579
Dawlish. the Auror.
has let slip that the Potter boy...

33
00:05:10.755 --> 00:05:13.849
...will not be moved
until the 30th of this month.

34
00:05:14.292 --> 00:05:15.554
The day before he turns 17.

35
00:05:15.726 --> 00:05:18.957
This is a false trail.

36
00:05:19.630 --> 00:05:23.794
The Auror Office no longer plays any part
in the protection of Harry Potter.

37
00:05:23.968 --> 00:05:28.337
Those closest to him believe
we have infiltrated the Ministry.

38
00:05:28.940 --> 00:05:30.532
Well. they got that right. haven't they?

39
00:05:30.708 --> 00:05:32.699
[ALL LAUGH]

40
00:05:35.012 --> 00:05:37.480
What say you. Pius?

41
00:05:41.018 --> 00:05:43.612
One hears many things. my Lord.

42
00:05:43.788 --> 00:05:46.348
Whether the truth is among them
is not clear.

43
00:05:46.524 --> 00:05:49.891
Heh. Spoken like a true politician.

44
00:05:50.061 --> 00:05:53.121
You will. I think.
prove most useful. Pius.

45
00:05:56.734 --> 00:05:59.965
- Where will he be taken. the boy?
SNAPE: To a safe house.

46
00:06:00.371 --> 00:06:02.999
Most likely the home of someone
in the Order.

47
00:06:03.174 --> 00:06:06.405
I'm told it's been given
every manner of protection possible.

48
00:06:06.577 --> 00:06:10.172
Once there.
it will be impractical to attack him.

49
00:06:10.348 --> 00:06:15.285
Ahem. My Lord.
I'd like to volunteer myself for this task.

50
00:06:15.453 --> 00:06:16.442
I want to kill the boy.

51
00:06:16.621 --> 00:06:17.610
[YELL IN DISTANCE]

52
00:06:17.788 --> 00:06:19.016
Wormtail!

53
00:06:19.190 --> 00:06:22.159
Have I not spoken to you
about keeping our guest quiet?

54
00:06:22.326 --> 00:06:24.226
Yes. my Lord.

55
00:06:24.395 --> 00:06:27.057
Right away. my Lord.

56
00:06:27.298 --> 00:06:31.792
VOLDEMORT: As inspiring
as I find your bloodlust. Bellatrix...

57
00:06:32.236 --> 00:06:35.535
...I must be the one to kill Harry Potter.

58
00:06:38.009 --> 00:06:42.810
But I face an unfortunate complication.

59
00:06:42.980 --> 00:06:48.179
That my wand and Potter's
share the same core.

60
00:06:49.420 --> 00:06:55.984
They are. in some ways. twins.

61
00:06:56.160 --> 00:07:00.859
We can wound.
but not fatally harm one another.

62
00:07:02.466 --> 00:07:05.264
If I am to kill him...

63
00:07:05.937 --> 00:07:09.703
...I must do it with another's wand.

64
00:07:11.709 --> 00:07:17.409
Come.
surely one of you would like the honor?

65
00:07:19.016 --> 00:07:20.677
Mm?

66
00:07:22.386 --> 00:07:27.187
What about you. Lucius?

67
00:07:29.694 --> 00:07:31.093
My Lord?

68
00:07:31.262 --> 00:07:33.230
"My Lord?"

69
00:07:34.298 --> 00:07:37.927
I require your wand.

70
00:07:51.248 --> 00:07:53.716
Do I detect elm?

71
00:07:53.884 --> 00:07:55.852
Yes. my Lord.

72
00:08:01.792 --> 00:08:04.727
And the core?

73
00:08:04.895 --> 00:08:07.090
Dragon. Ahem.

74
00:08:07.264 --> 00:08:08.891
Dragon heartstring. my Lord.

75
00:08:09.066 --> 00:08:11.261
- Dragon heartstring.
- Mm.

76
00:08:26.984 --> 00:08:28.747
VOLDEMORT:
To those of you who do not know...

77
00:08:28.919 --> 00:08:31.581
...we are joined tonight
by Miss Charity Burbage...

78
00:08:31.756 --> 00:08:37.251
...who. until recently. taught at Hogwarts
School of Witchcraft and Wizardry.

79
00:08:37.428 --> 00:08:40.886
Her specialty was Muggle Studies.

80
00:08:41.065 --> 00:08:43.056
[ALL CHUCKLE]

81
00:08:44.101 --> 00:08:50.370
It is Miss Burbage's belief
that Muggles are not so different from us.

82
00:08:50.541 --> 00:08:54.170
She would. given her way...

83
00:08:54.945 --> 00:08:56.879
...have us mate with them.

84
00:08:57.048 --> 00:08:59.039
[ALL CHUCKLE]

85
00:09:00.551 --> 00:09:06.751
To her. the mixture of magical
and Muggle blood is not an abomination...

86
00:09:06.924 --> 00:09:09.950
...but something to be encouraged.

87
00:09:11.028 --> 00:09:12.893
BURBAGE:
Severus.

88
00:09:13.064 --> 00:09:15.032
Severus. please.

89
00:09:16.700 --> 00:09:18.861
We're friends.

90
00:09:23.641 --> 00:09:25.199
<i>VOLDEMORT:
Avada Kedavra!

91
00:09:35.453 --> 00:09:37.478
Nagini.

92
00:09:41.092 --> 00:09:42.753
Dinner.

93
00:09:51.435 --> 00:09:52.595
[HISSES]

94
00:10:18.062 --> 00:10:20.530
[HEDWIG SCREECHES]

95
00:11:20.925 --> 00:11:22.916
[ENGINE WHIRRING THEN STOPS]

96
00:11:28.065 --> 00:11:31.466
HAGRID: Hello. Harry.
HARRY: All right. Wow.

97
00:11:31.635 --> 00:11:32.727
Hello.

98
00:11:32.903 --> 00:11:35.804
HAGRID: You're looking fit.
- Yeah. he's absolutely gorgeous.

99
00:11:35.973 --> 00:11:38.441
What say we get undercover
before someone murders him?

100
00:11:38.609 --> 00:11:39.633
HARRY:
Evening.

101
00:11:41.312 --> 00:11:42.973
[GRUNTS]

102
00:11:44.548 --> 00:11:46.948
HARRY: I thought you were
looking after the Prime Minister.

103
00:11:47.117 --> 00:11:49.017
You are more important.

104
00:11:49.186 --> 00:11:52.246
- Hello. Harry. Bill Weasley.
- Oh. Pleasure to meet you.

105
00:11:52.423 --> 00:11:55.415
FRED: He was never always this handsome.
- Dead ugly.

106
00:11:55.593 --> 00:11:56.992
True enough.

107
00:11:57.161 --> 00:11:59.686
Owe it all to a werewolf.
name of Greyback.

108
00:11:59.863 --> 00:12:03.230
- Hope to repay the favor one day.
- You're still beautiful to me. William.

109
00:12:03.601 --> 00:12:07.230
LUPIN: Just remember. Fleur.
Bill takes his steaks on the raw side now.

110
00:12:07.404 --> 00:12:09.736
My husband. the joker.

111
00:12:09.907 --> 00:12:13.172
By the way. wait till you hear the news.
Remus and I-

112
00:12:13.344 --> 00:12:15.778
All right. We'll have time
for a cozy catch-up later.

113
00:12:15.946 --> 00:12:18.915
We've got to get the hell out of here.
And soon.

114
00:12:19.583 --> 00:12:22.848
Potter. you're underage. which means
you've still got the Trace on you.

115
00:12:23.020 --> 00:12:24.044
What's the Trace?

116
00:12:24.221 --> 00:12:26.883
If you sneeze. the Ministry will know
who wipes your nose.

117
00:12:27.057 --> 00:12:30.220
We have to use those means of transport
the Trace can't detect:

118
00:12:30.394 --> 00:12:32.726
Brooms. Thestrals and the like.
We go in pairs.

119
00:12:32.896 --> 00:12:36.662
That way. if anyone's out there waiting
for us. and I reckon there will be...

120
00:12:36.834 --> 00:12:39.325
...they won't know which Harry Potter
is the real one.

121
00:12:39.770 --> 00:12:40.930
The real one?

122
00:12:42.273 --> 00:12:45.367
I believe you're familiar
with this particular brew.

123
00:12:45.542 --> 00:12:47.840
No. Absolutely not.

124
00:12:48.012 --> 00:12:49.343
I told you he'd take it well.

125
00:12:49.513 --> 00:12:52.641
No. if you think I'm gonna let everyone
risk their lives for me. I-

126
00:12:52.816 --> 00:12:55.876
- Never done that before. have we?
- No. No. This is different.

127
00:12:56.053 --> 00:12:58.044
I mean. taking that. becoming me. No.

128
00:12:58.222 --> 00:13:00.053
Well. none of us really fancy it. mate.

129
00:13:00.224 --> 00:13:04.388
Imagine if something went wrong. and
we ended up a scrawny. specky git forever.

130
00:13:04.561 --> 00:13:06.222
MOODY:
Everyone here is of age. Potter.

131
00:13:06.930 --> 00:13:08.363
They've all agreed to take the risk.

132
00:13:08.532 --> 00:13:09.556
[MUNDUNGUS CLEARS THROAT]

133
00:13:09.733 --> 00:13:12.634
Technically. I've been coerced.

134
00:13:12.803 --> 00:13:14.998
Mundungus Fletcher. Mr. Potter.

135
00:13:15.172 --> 00:13:17.732
- Always been a huge admirer.
- Nip it. Mundungus.

136
00:13:19.043 --> 00:13:21.534
All right. Granger. as discussed.

137
00:13:21.712 --> 00:13:24.442
- Blimey. Hermione.
MOODY: Straight in here. if you please.

138
00:13:34.291 --> 00:13:38.489
For those of you who haven't taken
Polyjuice Potion before. fair warning:

139
00:13:38.662 --> 00:13:40.289
It tastes like goblin piss.

140
00:13:40.464 --> 00:13:43.433
Have a lot of experiences with that.
do you. Mad-Eye?

141
00:13:44.335 --> 00:13:47.270
Just trying to diffuse the tension.

142
00:13:48.305 --> 00:13:50.102
Oh.

143
00:13:53.177 --> 00:13:54.940
Ugh.

144
00:13:55.245 --> 00:13:58.544
[ALL GRUNTING]

145
00:14:19.203 --> 00:14:21.262
BOTH:
Wow. we're identical.

146
00:14:21.438 --> 00:14:22.496
MOODY:
Not yet. you're not.

147
00:14:26.176 --> 00:14:28.736
GEORGE: Haven't got anything
a bit more sporting. have you?

148
00:14:28.912 --> 00:14:30.379
FRED:
I don't really fancy this color.

149
00:14:30.547 --> 00:14:33.345
MOODY: Well. fancy this. you're not you.
So shut it and strip.

150
00:14:33.517 --> 00:14:35.075
MUNDUNGUS:
All right. all right.

151
00:14:35.252 --> 00:14:36.810
You'll need to change too. Potter.

152
00:14:37.321 --> 00:14:39.949
FLEUR:
Bill. look away. I'm hideous.

153
00:14:40.124 --> 00:14:42.422
RON:
I knew she was lying about that tattoo.

154
00:14:42.593 --> 00:14:45.027
HERMIONE:
Harry. your eyesight really is awful.

155
00:14:45.195 --> 00:14:48.892
Right. then. We�ll be pairing off.
Each Potter will have a protector.

156
00:14:49.066 --> 00:14:52.365
Mundungus. stick tight to me.
I wanna keep an eye on you.

157
00:14:52.903 --> 00:14:54.734
- As for Harry-
ALL: Yes?

158
00:14:55.572 --> 00:14:56.971
The real Harry.

159
00:14:57.141 --> 00:14:59.507
- Where the devil are you. anyway?
- Here.

160
00:14:59.676 --> 00:15:01.644
MOODY:
You�ll ride with Hagrid.

161
00:15:01.812 --> 00:15:06.840
I brought you here 16 years ago when
you were no bigger than a Bowtruckle.

162
00:15:07.017 --> 00:15:09.918
Seems only right that I should be
the one to take you away now.

163
00:15:10.087 --> 00:15:13.022
Yes. it's all very touching. Let's go.

164
00:15:15.259 --> 00:15:17.250
[HEDWIG SCREECHING]

165
00:15:26.336 --> 00:15:30.238
MOODY: Head for the Burrows.
We�ll rendezvous there.

166
00:15:30.774 --> 00:15:32.833
On the count of three.

167
00:15:33.010 --> 00:15:34.739
Hold tight. Harry.

168
00:15:34.912 --> 00:15:36.709
MOODY:
One...

169
00:15:37.581 --> 00:15:39.378
...two...

170
00:15:45.789 --> 00:15:47.586
...three!

171
00:16:17.588 --> 00:16:20.751
DEATH EATER 1: Which one?
DEATH EATER 2: Where are you?

172
00:16:21.959 --> 00:16:23.688
He's on your right!

173
00:16:23.861 --> 00:16:25.488
He's over there!

174
00:16:25.662 --> 00:16:27.323
DEATH EATER 3:
Down!

175
00:16:32.803 --> 00:16:34.464
Hagrid. we have to help the others!

176
00:16:34.872 --> 00:16:37.773
I can't do that. Harry. Mad-Eye's orders.

177
00:16:44.715 --> 00:16:46.512
Hang on.

178
00:16:50.320 --> 00:16:52.379
<i>Stupefy!

179
00:16:59.630 --> 00:17:01.029
[HORN HONKS]

180
00:17:01.265 --> 00:17:02.630
[GASPS]

181
00:17:06.103 --> 00:17:07.195
Hang on. Harry.

182
00:17:08.906 --> 00:17:10.430
[GRUNTS]

183
00:17:17.114 --> 00:17:18.979
Hagrid.

184
00:17:31.328 --> 00:17:32.454
[SCREECHING]
[GRUNTS]

185
00:17:36.199 --> 00:17:38.463
HARRY:
No. No.

186
00:17:50.080 --> 00:17:52.674
[GROANING]

187
00:18:00.557 --> 00:18:02.548
<i>VOLDEMORT:
Harry.

188
00:18:29.052 --> 00:18:30.883
[YELLING]

189
00:18:52.809 --> 00:18:55.175
[RUMBLING]

190
00:19:04.855 --> 00:19:06.288
[GRUNTS]

191
00:19:22.506 --> 00:19:25.566
MOLLY:
Harry. Hagrid.

192
00:19:26.977 --> 00:19:30.435
What happened? Where are the others?

193
00:19:30.614 --> 00:19:31.774
Is no one else back?

194
00:19:31.948 --> 00:19:35.509
HAGRID: They were on us right from
the start. Molly. We didn't stand a chance.

195
00:19:35.686 --> 00:19:38.849
Well. thank goodness
you two are all right.

196
00:19:39.022 --> 00:19:41.582
HAGRID: The Death Eaters were
waiting for us. It was an ambush.

197
00:19:41.758 --> 00:19:44.158
GINNY: Ron and Tonks
should�ve already been back.

198
00:19:44.327 --> 00:19:45.521
Dad and Fred as well.

199
00:19:48.465 --> 00:19:50.126
LUPIN:
Here!

200
00:19:50.767 --> 00:19:54.203
Quick. Into the house.

201
00:19:57.874 --> 00:19:59.933
Oh. my boy.

202
00:20:02.112 --> 00:20:04.603
Oh. Oh.

203
00:20:05.015 --> 00:20:06.039
[BOTH GRUNT]

204
00:20:06.216 --> 00:20:07.513
- Lupin!
GINNY: What are you doing?

205
00:20:10.053 --> 00:20:12.988
What creature sat in the corner...

206
00:20:13.156 --> 00:20:16.455
...the first time Harry Potter
visited my office in Hogwarts?

207
00:20:16.626 --> 00:20:18.253
- Are you mad?
- What creature?!

208
00:20:18.428 --> 00:20:20.259
A Grindylow.

209
00:20:23.734 --> 00:20:25.998
[HARRY SIGHS]

210
00:20:26.603 --> 00:20:28.264
LUPIN:
We've been betrayed.

211
00:20:28.438 --> 00:20:30.838
Voldemort knew
you were being moved tonight.

212
00:20:31.007 --> 00:20:33.908
I had to make sure
you weren't an impostor.

213
00:20:36.580 --> 00:20:38.047
[WHOOSH IN DISTANCE]

214
00:20:41.051 --> 00:20:42.484
Wait.

215
00:20:45.489 --> 00:20:50.017
The last words Albus Dumbledore spoke
to the pair of us?

216
00:20:51.828 --> 00:20:56.197
"Harry is the best hope we have.
Trust him. "

217
00:21:00.737 --> 00:21:01.829
What gave you away?

218
00:21:02.005 --> 00:21:05.202
Hedwig. I think.
She was trying to protect me.

219
00:21:21.758 --> 00:21:22.918
Thanks.

220
00:21:23.093 --> 00:21:25.254
TONKS:
Deserves that. Brilliant. he was.

221
00:21:25.428 --> 00:21:28.522
- I wouldn�t be standing here without him.
HERMIONE: Really?

222
00:21:29.533 --> 00:21:32.195
Always the tone of surprise.

223
00:21:40.410 --> 00:21:41.604
We the last back?

224
00:21:42.913 --> 00:21:43.937
FRED:
Where's George?

225
00:22:05.235 --> 00:22:07.465
How you feeling. Georgie?

226
00:22:09.472 --> 00:22:10.996
Saint-like.

227
00:22:12.209 --> 00:22:13.437
Come again?

228
00:22:14.377 --> 00:22:17.938
Saint-like. I'm holy.

229
00:22:18.448 --> 00:22:21.508
I'm holey. Fred. Get it?

230
00:22:23.320 --> 00:22:28.019
The whole wide world of ear-related humor
and you go for "I'm holey. "

231
00:22:28.191 --> 00:22:29.351
That's pathetic.

232
00:22:29.960 --> 00:22:32.258
Reckon I'm still better-looking than you.

233
00:22:35.799 --> 00:22:37.994
Mad-Eye's dead.

234
00:22:48.378 --> 00:22:52.109
Mundungus took one look at Voldemort
and Disapparated.

235
00:23:15.038 --> 00:23:17.063
<i>MOODY:
Head for the Burrows.

236
00:23:17.874 --> 00:23:19.239
<i>DUMBLEDORE:
This is beyond anything I imagined.

237
00:23:19.409 --> 00:23:22.037
<i>SLUGHORN: Seven?
RIDDLE: Seven...? A Horcrux.

238
00:23:22.212 --> 00:23:23.645
<i>HARRY:
They could be hidden anywhere.

239
00:23:23.813 --> 00:23:26.008
<i>SLUGHORN:
To rip the soul into seven pieces...

240
00:23:26.182 --> 00:23:29.151
<i>HARRY: If you did destroy each Horcrux...
DUMBLEDORE: One destroys Voldemort.

241
00:23:32.756 --> 00:23:34.383
<i>Trust me.

242
00:23:35.325 --> 00:23:38.886
<i>VOLDEMORT:
You lied to me. Lied to me. Ollivander.

243
00:23:39.062 --> 00:23:40.154
[GRUNTS]

244
00:24:10.827 --> 00:24:12.761
RON:
Going somewhere?

245
00:24:16.433 --> 00:24:20.529
Nobody else is going to die. Not for me.

246
00:24:20.704 --> 00:24:22.501
For you?

247
00:24:22.672 --> 00:24:24.902
You think Mad-Eye died for you?

248
00:24:25.075 --> 00:24:28.010
You think George took that curse
for you?

249
00:24:28.778 --> 00:24:32.714
You may be the Chosen One. mate.
but this is a whole lot bigger than that.

250
00:24:32.882 --> 00:24:35.407
It's always been bigger than that.

251
00:24:37.620 --> 00:24:40.111
- Come with me.
- What. and leave Hermione?

252
00:24:40.590 --> 00:24:44.822
You mad?
We wouldn�t last two days without her.

253
00:24:46.229 --> 00:24:47.753
Don't tell her I said that.

254
00:24:49.332 --> 00:24:52.529
Besides.
you've still got the Trace on you.

255
00:24:52.702 --> 00:24:56.798
- We've still got the wedding-
- I don't care about a wedding.

256
00:24:56.973 --> 00:25:01.842
I'm sorry. No matter whose it is.
I have to start finding these Horcruxes.

257
00:25:02.012 --> 00:25:03.980
They're our only chance to beat him...

258
00:25:04.147 --> 00:25:07.116
...and the longer we stay here.
the stronger he gets.

259
00:25:08.551 --> 00:25:10.644
Tonight's not the night. mate.

260
00:25:10.954 --> 00:25:13.422
We'd only be doing him a favor.

261
00:25:23.033 --> 00:25:24.057
[HARRY SIGHS]

262
00:25:24.234 --> 00:25:25.895
[BAG THUDS]

263
00:25:41.184 --> 00:25:43.118
Do you think he knows?

264
00:25:43.853 --> 00:25:49.723
I mean. they're bits of his soul.
these Horcruxes. Bits of him.

265
00:25:50.460 --> 00:25:54.726
When Dumbledore destroyed the ring.
you destroyed Tom Riddle�s diary...

266
00:25:56.232 --> 00:25:58.826
...he must have felt something.

267
00:25:59.602 --> 00:26:03.333
To kill the other Horcruxes.
we have to find them.

268
00:26:03.706 --> 00:26:05.674
Where are they?

269
00:26:06.209 --> 00:26:08.268
Where do we start?

270
00:26:11.714 --> 00:26:12.806
FRED:
Ready when you are.

271
00:26:12.982 --> 00:26:14.381
[RON & FRED GRUNTING]

272
00:26:14.551 --> 00:26:18.851
ARTHUR: Please pay attention!
It's your brother's wedding. Buck up.

273
00:26:44.280 --> 00:26:46.339
GINNY:
Zip me up. will you?

274
00:27:00.196 --> 00:27:02.130
It seems silly. doesn't it. a wedding?

275
00:27:02.632 --> 00:27:04.998
Given everything that's going on.

276
00:27:06.336 --> 00:27:08.395
Maybe that's the best reason to have it...

277
00:27:09.005 --> 00:27:11.530
...because of everything that's going on.

278
00:27:27.590 --> 00:27:29.751
GEORGE:
Morning.

279
00:27:39.936 --> 00:27:42.097
ARTHUR:
Come on. keep up.

280
00:27:42.772 --> 00:27:44.433
All together now.

281
00:27:44.607 --> 00:27:50.045
One. two. three.

282
00:28:00.123 --> 00:28:02.557
How's it looking at your end. boys?

283
00:28:03.193 --> 00:28:05.127
FRED & GEORGE:
Brilliant.

284
00:28:07.230 --> 00:28:12.065
Bloody hell.
What's the Minister of Magic doing here?

285
00:28:17.974 --> 00:28:19.839
To what do we owe the pleasure.
Minister?

286
00:28:20.009 --> 00:28:24.571
I think we both know the answer
to that question. Mr. Potter.

287
00:28:32.255 --> 00:28:34.155
And this is...?

288
00:28:42.198 --> 00:28:46.100
SCRIMGEOUR: "Herein is set forth
the last will and testament...

289
00:28:46.269 --> 00:28:50.865
...of Albus Percival Wulfric
Brian Dumbledore.

290
00:28:51.040 --> 00:28:55.500
First. to Ronald Bilius Weasley...

291
00:28:55.678 --> 00:28:58.977
...I leave my Deluminator...

292
00:28:59.148 --> 00:29:01.412
...a device of my own making...

293
00:29:01.584 --> 00:29:06.817
...in the hope that.
when things seem most dark...

294
00:29:08.458 --> 00:29:11.325
...it will show him the light. "

295
00:29:17.233 --> 00:29:20.327
- Dumbledore left this for me?
- Yeah.

296
00:29:21.271 --> 00:29:22.863
Brillliant.

297
00:29:23.906 --> 00:29:25.737
What is it?

298
00:29:37.887 --> 00:29:39.479
Wicked.

299
00:29:41.791 --> 00:29:44.760
"To Hermione Jean Granger...

300
00:29:44.927 --> 00:29:50.092
<i>...I leave my copy of
The Tales of Beedle the Bard...

301
00:29:50.266 --> 00:29:54.930
...in the hope that she find it
entertaining and instructive. "

302
00:29:55.738 --> 00:29:57.069
RON:
Mom used to read me those.

303
00:29:57.940 --> 00:29:59.464
"The Wizard and the Hopping Pot. "

304
00:29:59.642 --> 00:30:02.577
"Babbitty Rabbitty
and the Cackling Stump. "

305
00:30:04.347 --> 00:30:07.714
Come on. Babbitty Rabbitty.

306
00:30:08.184 --> 00:30:09.879
No?

307
00:30:10.219 --> 00:30:13.017
"To Harry James Potter...

308
00:30:13.556 --> 00:30:17.287
...I leave the Snitch he caught
in his first Quidditch match at Hogwarts...

309
00:30:17.460 --> 00:30:22.488
...as a reminder
of the rewards of perseverance...

310
00:30:24.734 --> 00:30:26.929
...and skill. "

311
00:30:46.989 --> 00:30:50.049
- Is that it. then?
- Not quite.

312
00:30:50.226 --> 00:30:55.630
Dumbledore left you a second bequest:

313
00:30:55.865 --> 00:30:58.857
The sword of Godric Gryffindor.

314
00:31:00.470 --> 00:31:05.066
Unfortunately. the sword of Gryffindor
was not Dumbledore�s to give away.

315
00:31:05.475 --> 00:31:08.205
As an important historical artifact.
it belongs-

316
00:31:08.378 --> 00:31:09.470
HERMIONE:
To Harry.

317
00:31:10.313 --> 00:31:12.247
It belongs to Harry.

318
00:31:12.415 --> 00:31:15.111
It came to him when he needed it
in the Chamber of Secrets.

319
00:31:15.284 --> 00:31:18.185
The sword may present itself
to any worthy Gryffindor.

320
00:31:18.354 --> 00:31:20.686
That does not make it
that wizard's property.

321
00:31:22.125 --> 00:31:25.754
And. in any event. the current
whereabouts of the sword are unknown.

322
00:31:25.928 --> 00:31:28.522
HARRY: Excuse me?
- The sword is missing.

323
00:31:29.899 --> 00:31:33.426
I don't know what you're up to.
Mr. Potter...

324
00:31:33.603 --> 00:31:37.562
...but you can't fight this war
on your own.

325
00:31:37.740 --> 00:31:40.140
He's too strong.

326
00:31:46.215 --> 00:31:48.206
[FOLK MUSIC PLAYING]

327
00:32:41.337 --> 00:32:42.599
LUNA:
Hello. Harry.

328
00:32:43.506 --> 00:32:47.499
I've interrupted a deep thought. haven't I?
I can see it growing smaller in your eyes.

329
00:32:47.677 --> 00:32:49.201
Of course not. How are you. Luna?

330
00:32:49.378 --> 00:32:52.006
Very well. Got bitten by a garden gnome
only moments ago.

331
00:32:52.181 --> 00:32:54.513
Gnome saliva is very beneficial.

332
00:32:54.684 --> 00:32:57.050
Xenophilius Lovegood.
We live just over the hill.

333
00:32:57.220 --> 00:32:58.414
Pleasure to meet you. sir.

334
00:32:58.588 --> 00:33:01.352
<i>I trust you know. Mr. Potter.
that we at The Quibbler...

335
00:33:01.524 --> 00:33:03.856
<i>...unlike those toadies
at The Daily Prophet...

336
00:33:04.026 --> 00:33:06.620
...fully supported Dumbledore
in his lifetime...

337
00:33:06.796 --> 00:33:10.459
...and. in his death.
support you just as fully.

338
00:33:10.766 --> 00:33:12.131
Thank you.

339
00:33:12.301 --> 00:33:15.134
Come. Daddy.
Harry doesn't want to talk to us right now.

340
00:33:15.304 --> 00:33:17.602
He's just too polite to say so.

341
00:33:17.773 --> 00:33:19.832
XENOPHILIUS:
Harry Potter.

342
00:33:23.379 --> 00:33:25.506
Excuse me. sir? May I sit down?

343
00:33:25.681 --> 00:33:29.082
Mr. Potter. By all means. Here.

344
00:33:29.252 --> 00:33:30.913
HARRY:
Thanks.

345
00:33:33.623 --> 00:33:36.922
<i>I found what you wrote
in The Daily Prophet really moving.

346
00:33:37.493 --> 00:33:40.291
You obviously knew Dumbledore well.

347
00:33:40.463 --> 00:33:43.398
Well. I certainly knew him the longest.

348
00:33:43.566 --> 00:33:46.296
That is. if you don't count his brother.
Aberforth...

349
00:33:46.469 --> 00:33:49.495
...and somehow. people never do
seem to count Aberforth.

350
00:33:49.839 --> 00:33:51.898
- I didn't even know he had a brother.
- Ah.

351
00:33:52.074 --> 00:33:55.635
Well. Dumbledore was always
very private. even as a boy.

352
00:33:55.811 --> 00:33:57.210
Don't despair. Elphias.

353
00:33:57.380 --> 00:34:01.817
I'm told he's been thoroughly
unriddled by Rita Skeeter...

354
00:34:01.984 --> 00:34:04.817
...in 800 pages. no less.

355
00:34:05.454 --> 00:34:09.857
Word has it that someone talked to her.

356
00:34:10.026 --> 00:34:12.824
Someone who knew
the Dumbledore family well.

357
00:34:13.229 --> 00:34:16.824
Both you and I know who that is.
Elphias.

358
00:34:16.999 --> 00:34:18.466
A monstrous betrayal.

359
00:34:20.369 --> 00:34:21.961
Who are we talking about?

360
00:34:23.439 --> 00:34:25.566
Bathilda Bagshot.

361
00:34:27.243 --> 00:34:28.301
- Who?
MURIEL: My God. boy...

362
00:34:28.477 --> 00:34:33.244
...she's only the most celebrated
magical historian of the last century.

363
00:34:34.951 --> 00:34:39.183
She was as close
to the Dumbledores as anyone.

364
00:34:39.355 --> 00:34:44.383
Oh. I'm sure Rita Skeeter thought
it well worth a trip to Godric's Hollow...

365
00:34:44.560 --> 00:34:47.757
...to take a peek
into that old bird's rattled cage.

366
00:34:47.930 --> 00:34:49.761
Godric's Hollow?

367
00:34:50.199 --> 00:34:52.099
Bathilda Bagshot
lives at Godric's Hollow?

368
00:34:52.501 --> 00:34:54.594
Well. that's where
she first met Dumbledore.

369
00:34:54.770 --> 00:34:56.635
You don't mean to say
he lived there too?

370
00:34:56.806 --> 00:35:00.367
The family moved there
after his father killed those three Muggles.

371
00:35:00.543 --> 00:35:04.172
Oh. it was quite the scandal.

372
00:35:04.347 --> 00:35:09.182
Honestly. my boy.
are you sure you knew him at all?

373
00:35:27.970 --> 00:35:29.961
[GASPING AND MURMURING]

374
00:35:35.645 --> 00:35:38.739
<i>SHACKLEBOLT:
The Ministry has fallen.

375
00:35:39.382 --> 00:35:43.284
<i>The Minister of Magic is dead.

376
00:35:45.755 --> 00:35:48.053
<i>[WHISPERING]
They are coming.

377
00:35:48.224 --> 00:35:50.317
<i>They are coming.

378
00:35:51.594 --> 00:35:53.084
<i>They are coming.

379
00:35:53.262 --> 00:35:54.729
WOMAN 1:
They're coming!

380
00:35:56.766 --> 00:35:58.597
Nice meeting you. Mr. Potter.

381
00:35:59.168 --> 00:36:00.795
[WOMAN 2 SHRIEKS]

382
00:36:09.679 --> 00:36:12.045
HARRY: Ginny!
- Harry! Go!

383
00:36:12.214 --> 00:36:13.272
Go!

384
00:36:15.418 --> 00:36:17.648
[HORN HONKS]

385
00:36:26.595 --> 00:36:29.189
Here you go. sightseeing tour?
Leaves in 15 minutes.

386
00:36:30.633 --> 00:36:33.261
- Where are we?
- Shaftesbury Avenue.

387
00:36:33.436 --> 00:36:36.633
I used to come to the theater here
with Mom and Dad.

388
00:36:36.939 --> 00:36:40.033
I don't know why I thought of it.
It just popped into my head.

389
00:36:40.443 --> 00:36:42.274
This way.

390
00:36:46.082 --> 00:36:48.175
HERMIONE:
We need to change.

391
00:36:54.123 --> 00:36:55.385
RON:
How the ruddy...?

392
00:36:55.558 --> 00:36:58.118
Undetectable Extension Charm.

393
00:36:58.561 --> 00:37:00.825
You're amazing. you are.

394
00:37:01.030 --> 00:37:03.590
Always the tone of surprise.

395
00:37:03.766 --> 00:37:05.427
[THUD]

396
00:37:05.601 --> 00:37:07.728
Ah. That'll be the books.

397
00:37:13.242 --> 00:37:15.107
What about all the people
at the wedding?

398
00:37:15.277 --> 00:37:17.745
- Do you think we should go back?
- They were after you.

399
00:37:17.913 --> 00:37:20.074
We'd put everyone in danger
by going back.

400
00:37:20.249 --> 00:37:21.773
[MUFFLED MUSIC
PLAYING OVER HEADPHONES]

401
00:37:21.951 --> 00:37:23.680
- Ron's right.
WAITRESS: Ahem.

402
00:37:23.853 --> 00:37:25.514
Coffee?

403
00:37:26.055 --> 00:37:29.081
HERMIONE: A cappuccino. please.
- You?

404
00:37:29.925 --> 00:37:33.224
- What she said.
- Same.

405
00:37:36.599 --> 00:37:40.433
So where do we go from here?
Leaky Cauldron?

406
00:37:40.803 --> 00:37:41.895
It's too dangerous.

407
00:37:42.805 --> 00:37:46.332
If Voldemort has taken over the Ministry.
none of the old places are safe.

408
00:37:46.509 --> 00:37:49.569
Everyone from the wedding
will have gone underground. into hiding.

409
00:37:49.745 --> 00:37:52.236
My rucksack with all my things.
I've left it at the Burrow.

410
00:37:52.414 --> 00:37:54.405
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

411
00:37:57.386 --> 00:37:59.286
You're joking.

412
00:37:59.622 --> 00:38:00.714
[SIGHS]

413
00:38:00.890 --> 00:38:04.849
I've had all the essentials packed
for days. just in case.

414
00:38:05.027 --> 00:38:07.222
RON:
By the way. these jeans. not my favorite.

415
00:38:08.397 --> 00:38:09.455
HARRY:
Down!

416
00:38:10.599 --> 00:38:11.896
<i>Stupefy!

417
00:38:13.102 --> 00:38:14.763
[SINGING INDISTINCTLY]

418
00:38:16.105 --> 00:38:17.834
<i>DOLOHOV:
Expulso!

419
00:38:26.081 --> 00:38:27.571
[GRUNTS]

420
00:38:27.750 --> 00:38:29.581
<i>Petrificus Totalus.

421
00:38:33.722 --> 00:38:34.780
Go.

422
00:38:35.224 --> 00:38:36.384
Leave.

423
00:38:41.063 --> 00:38:43.861
HARRY:
Lock the door. get the lights.

424
00:38:51.540 --> 00:38:52.939
[GLASS RATTLING]

425
00:38:53.108 --> 00:38:54.837
This one's name is Rowle.

426
00:38:55.344 --> 00:38:58.780
He was on the Astronomy Tower
the night Snape killed Dumbledore.

427
00:38:59.582 --> 00:39:04.076
This is Dolohov. I recognize him
from the wanted posters.

428
00:39:05.154 --> 00:39:07.315
So. what we gonna do with you. hey?

429
00:39:08.190 --> 00:39:10.283
Kill us if it was turned round.
wouldn�t you?

430
00:39:10.459 --> 00:39:11.790
HARRY:
If we kill them. they'll know we were here.

431
00:39:11.961 --> 00:39:13.360
HERMIONE:
Ron.

432
00:39:13.529 --> 00:39:17.488
Suppose he did Mad-Eye.
How would you feel then?

433
00:39:19.468 --> 00:39:21.095
It's better we wipe their memories.

434
00:39:21.971 --> 00:39:23.939
You're the boss.

435
00:39:24.240 --> 00:39:26.003
Hermione...

436
00:39:28.477 --> 00:39:30.945
...you're the best at spells.

437
00:39:48.597 --> 00:39:50.792
<i>Obliviate.

438
00:40:03.145 --> 00:40:04.737
HARRY:
How is it they knew we were there?

439
00:40:04.914 --> 00:40:06.506
HERMIONE:
Maybe you still have the Trace on you?

440
00:40:06.682 --> 00:40:10.118
Can't be. Trace breaks at 17.
It's wizarding law.

441
00:40:10.719 --> 00:40:11.743
[HERMIONE GASPS]

442
00:40:11.921 --> 00:40:13.479
What?

443
00:40:14.290 --> 00:40:17.259
We didn't celebrate your birthday. Harry.

444
00:40:17.626 --> 00:40:20.891
Ginny and I. we prepared a cake.

445
00:40:21.063 --> 00:40:24.032
We were going to bring it out
at the end of the wedding.

446
00:40:24.199 --> 00:40:27.635
I appreciate the thought. but given the fact
that we were almost killed...

447
00:40:27.803 --> 00:40:30.203
...by a couple of Death Eaters
a few minutes ago...

448
00:40:31.874 --> 00:40:33.569
Right.

449
00:40:34.376 --> 00:40:35.400
Perspective.

450
00:40:35.577 --> 00:40:38.569
We need to get off the streets.
get somewhere safe.

451
00:41:05.474 --> 00:41:06.736
[HERMIONE SHRIEKS]

452
00:41:11.680 --> 00:41:13.705
What was that all about?

453
00:41:14.683 --> 00:41:20.519
Probably Mad-Eye's idea.
in case Snape decided to come snooping.

454
00:41:22.324 --> 00:41:23.985
[CLATTERING]

455
00:41:28.697 --> 00:41:30.665
<i>Homenum Revelio.

456
00:41:37.306 --> 00:41:39.137
We're alone.

457
00:41:45.948 --> 00:41:48.178
<i>OLLIVANDER:
I believed another wand-

458
00:41:48.350 --> 00:41:50.818
<i>VOLDEMORT: You lied to me.
OLLIVANDER: It makes no sense.

459
00:41:51.653 --> 00:41:53.484
[OLLIVANDER GRUNTING]

460
00:41:53.655 --> 00:41:56.624
I believed a different wand would work.
I swear.

461
00:41:58.127 --> 00:42:00.186
There must be another way.

462
00:42:15.744 --> 00:42:16.836
[CLATTERING]

463
00:43:09.198 --> 00:43:10.358
[DOOR OPENS]

464
00:43:10.532 --> 00:43:14.263
RON:
Harry? Hermione. where are you?

465
00:43:14.536 --> 00:43:16.868
I think I've found something.

466
00:43:23.178 --> 00:43:24.236
Lovely.

467
00:43:29.918 --> 00:43:33.410
"Regulus Arcturus Black. "

468
00:43:33.589 --> 00:43:35.284
R.A.B.

469
00:43:38.894 --> 00:43:42.193
HARRY: "I know I will be dead
long before you read this.

470
00:43:42.364 --> 00:43:46.391
I have stolen the real Horcrux
and intend to destroy it. "

471
00:43:46.768 --> 00:43:49.168
R.A.B. is Sirius's brother.

472
00:43:49.605 --> 00:43:51.368
Yes.

473
00:43:53.475 --> 00:43:57.343
Question is.
did he actually destroy the real Horcrux?

474
00:43:57.646 --> 00:43:59.705
[CLATTERING]

475
00:44:16.498 --> 00:44:18.659
[KREACHER GRUNTING]

476
00:44:19.067 --> 00:44:21.228
You've been spying on us. have you?

477
00:44:21.403 --> 00:44:25.863
KREACHER:
Kreacher has been watching.

478
00:44:26.041 --> 00:44:27.975
HERMIONE:
Maybe he knows where the real locket is.

479
00:44:30.979 --> 00:44:32.913
HARRY:
Have you ever seen this before?

480
00:44:33.081 --> 00:44:34.673
Kreacher?

481
00:44:35.517 --> 00:44:37.951
It's Master Regulus' locket.

482
00:44:38.120 --> 00:44:40.816
HARRY:
But there were two. weren't there?

483
00:44:41.823 --> 00:44:43.518
Where's the other one?

484
00:44:43.825 --> 00:44:45.816
[KREACHER WHIMPERS]

485
00:44:46.028 --> 00:44:50.590
Kreacher doesn't know
where the other locket is.

486
00:44:50.766 --> 00:44:53.166
Yes. but did you ever see it?
Was it in this house?

487
00:44:53.335 --> 00:44:54.495
Filthy Mudblood.

488
00:44:54.670 --> 00:44:56.365
- Death Eaters are coming-
- Ron.

489
00:44:56.538 --> 00:44:59.371
KREACHER: Blood traitor. Weasley.
- Answer her.

490
00:45:01.143 --> 00:45:03.373
Yes.

491
00:45:04.413 --> 00:45:07.871
It was here in this house.

492
00:45:09.151 --> 00:45:11.483
A most evil object.

493
00:45:11.653 --> 00:45:12.881
How do you mean?

494
00:45:13.655 --> 00:45:17.955
Before Master Regulus died.
he ordered Kreacher to destroy it...

495
