966
01:25:25.719 --> 01:25:27.710
[BELL TOLLING]

967
01:25:34.094 --> 01:25:37.086
MAN:
Good night. Ha-ha-ha.

968
01:25:40.133 --> 01:25:42.897
Harry. I think it's Christmas Eve.

969
01:25:44.404 --> 01:25:45.701
Listen.

970
01:25:45.872 --> 01:25:47.863
[CHOIR SINGING INDISTINCTLY]

971
01:25:51.411 --> 01:25:54.244
Do you think they'd be in there.
Hermione?

972
01:25:54.681 --> 01:25:56.672
My mom and dad.

973
01:26:02.622 --> 01:26:04.886
Yeah. I think they would.

974
01:26:41.461 --> 01:26:44.521
HERMIONE:
"Ignotus Peverell. "

975
01:26:46.599 --> 01:26:48.226
Hey. Harry?

976
01:27:26.105 --> 01:27:28.300
Merry Christmas. Hermione.

977
01:27:29.609 --> 01:27:31.839
Merry Christmas. Harry.

978
01:27:51.698 --> 01:27:57.102
[WHISPERS] Harry. there's someone
watching us. By the church.

979
01:28:07.814 --> 01:28:09.645
I think I know who that is.

980
01:28:11.517 --> 01:28:12.950
HERMIONE:
I don't like this. Harry.

981
01:28:13.119 --> 01:28:18.147
HARRY [WHISPERS]: Hermione. she knew
Dumbledore. She might have the sword.

982
01:28:37.010 --> 01:28:38.637
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
This is where they died. Hermione.

983
01:28:46.219 --> 01:28:48.687
This is where he murdered them.

984
01:28:56.129 --> 01:28:58.120
[FLY BUZZES]

985
01:29:01.200 --> 01:29:03.134
You're Bathilda. aren't you?

986
01:29:08.741 --> 01:29:10.834
HARRY:
Here. let me do that.

987
01:29:34.968 --> 01:29:38.870
Miss Bagshot. who is this man?

988
01:29:50.483 --> 01:29:52.144
[WHISPERS]
Harry.

989
01:29:56.189 --> 01:29:58.054
<i>HARRY:
Lumos.

990
01:30:11.304 --> 01:30:13.295
[INSECT BUZZES]

991
01:30:38.164 --> 01:30:40.826
[CHITTERS]

992
01:30:45.838 --> 01:30:47.829
[SPEAKING IN PARSELTONGUE]

993
01:30:52.011 --> 01:30:53.945
[SPEAKING IN PARSELTONGUE]

994
01:31:05.158 --> 01:31:07.149
[INSECTS BUZZING]

995
01:31:34.454 --> 01:31:36.183
[HISSING]

996
01:31:38.424 --> 01:31:39.448
HERMIONE [IN NORMAL VOICE]:
Harry!

997
01:31:40.159 --> 01:31:41.285
[GRUNTING]

998
01:31:45.565 --> 01:31:46.589
[GRUNTS]

999
01:31:52.839 --> 01:31:54.830
[HARRY PANTING]

1000
01:31:57.743 --> 01:31:59.176
[YELLS]

1001
01:32:30.276 --> 01:32:31.334
<i>Confringo!

1002
01:33:07.813 --> 01:33:09.804
[HARRY SIGHING]

1003
01:33:14.086 --> 01:33:16.213
Are you feeling better?

1004
01:33:19.292 --> 01:33:21.760
You've outdone yourself this time.
Hermione.

1005
01:33:21.928 --> 01:33:24.021
The Forest of Dean.

1006
01:33:24.997 --> 01:33:29.366
I came here once with Mom and Dad.
years ago.

1007
01:33:30.002 --> 01:33:32.129
It's just how I remember it.

1008
01:33:32.538 --> 01:33:36.474
The trees. the river. everything.

1009
01:33:36.776 --> 01:33:39.609
Like nothing's changed.

1010
01:33:40.846 --> 01:33:43.838
Not true. of course.
Everything's changed.

1011
01:33:44.817 --> 01:33:48.617
If I brought my parents back here now.
they probably wouldn�t recognize any of it.

1012
01:33:50.723 --> 01:33:54.853
Not the trees. not the river...

1013
01:33:56.629 --> 01:33:58.756
...not even me.

1014
01:34:03.903 --> 01:34:06.701
Maybe we should just stay here. Harry.

1015
01:34:08.708 --> 01:34:10.835
Grow old.

1016
01:34:16.849 --> 01:34:20.148
You wanted to know
who the boy in the photograph was.

1017
01:34:20.886 --> 01:34:21.978
I know.

1018
01:34:23.155 --> 01:34:25.555
Gellert Grindelwald.

1019
01:34:32.498 --> 01:34:35.899
HARRY: He's the thief I saw
in Gregorovitch's Wand Shop.

1020
01:34:36.068 --> 01:34:39.333
Speaking of which. where is my wand?

1021
01:34:40.673 --> 01:34:43.073
Where's my wand. Hermione?

1022
01:34:51.717 --> 01:34:56.211
As we were leaving Godric's Hollow.
I cast a curse and it rebounded.

1023
01:34:58.958 --> 01:35:00.186
I'm sorry.

1024
01:35:00.860 --> 01:35:03.488
- I tried to mend it. but wands are different.
- It's done.

1025
01:35:05.464 --> 01:35:09.423
Leave me yours.
Go inside and get warm.

1026
01:35:09.835 --> 01:35:12.167
I'll take the locket as well.

1027
01:35:24.717 --> 01:35:26.082
<i>DUMBLEDORE:
Trust me.

1028
01:36:51.837 --> 01:36:53.464
<i>HARRY:
Lumos.

1029
01:37:34.547 --> 01:37:35.912
<i>Accio sword.

1030
01:37:41.754 --> 01:37:43.654
<i>Diffindo.

1031
01:38:11.450 --> 01:38:13.441
[PANTING]

1032
01:38:38.777 --> 01:38:40.768
[MUFFLED GRUNTING]

1033
01:39:14.547 --> 01:39:16.139
[HARRY GASPS THEN PANTING]

1034
01:39:24.089 --> 01:39:27.252
HARRY: Hermione?
- Are you mental?

1035
01:39:28.460 --> 01:39:30.018
It was you?

1036
01:39:30.195 --> 01:39:33.961
Well. yeah. Bit obvious. I think.

1037
01:39:34.133 --> 01:39:35.930
And you cast the doe as well. did you?

1038
01:39:36.502 --> 01:39:40.165
- No. I thought that was you.
- No. my Patronus is a stag.

1039
01:39:40.339 --> 01:39:42.534
Right. Yeah. Antlers.

1040
01:39:45.711 --> 01:39:48.874
HARRY:
Okay. Ron. Do it.

1041
01:39:49.848 --> 01:39:53.579
I can't handle it. That thing affects me
more than it affects you and Hermione.

1042
01:39:54.119 --> 01:39:56.747
- All the more reason.
- No. I can't.

1043
01:39:56.922 --> 01:39:58.150
Then why are you here?

1044
01:39:59.558 --> 01:40:01.617
Why did you come back?

1045
01:40:09.201 --> 01:40:13.331
Now. I'll have to speak to it in order for it
to open. When it does. don't hesitate.

1046
01:40:13.939 --> 01:40:16.464
I don't know what's in there.
but it'll put up a fight.

1047
01:40:16.642 --> 01:40:19.338
The bit of Riddle that was in that diary
tried to kill me.

1048
01:40:19.511 --> 01:40:21.376
[CHITTERING]

1049
01:40:21.814 --> 01:40:23.441
All right.

1050
01:40:24.283 --> 01:40:25.841
One...

1051
01:40:26.518 --> 01:40:27.576
...two...

1052
01:40:28.253 --> 01:40:30.153
...three.

1053
01:40:30.322 --> 01:40:32.313
[SPEAKING IN PARSELTONGUE]

1054
01:40:33.792 --> 01:40:36.090
[SNARLS THEN ROARING]

1055
01:40:36.261 --> 01:40:38.525
[HIGH-PITCHED WHISTLING]

1056
01:40:40.399 --> 01:40:45.496
<i>VOLDEMORT:
I have seen your heart. and it is mine.

1057
01:40:48.107 --> 01:40:52.009
<i>I have seen your dreams.
Ronald Weasley...

1058
01:40:52.177 --> 01:40:54.577
<i>...and I have seen your fears.

1059
01:40:56.281 --> 01:41:00.445
<i>Least loved by your mother.
who craved a daughter.

1060
01:41:01.086 --> 01:41:06.080
<i>Least loved by the girl
who prefers your friend.

1061
01:41:06.258 --> 01:41:08.988
HARRY:
Ron. kill it!

1062
01:41:15.434 --> 01:41:18.130
We were better without you.

1063
01:41:18.637 --> 01:41:20.366
Happier without you.

1064
01:41:20.539 --> 01:41:25.909
Who could look at you
compared to Harry Potter?

1065
01:41:27.146 --> 01:41:30.479
What are you
compared with the Chosen One?

1066
01:41:30.649 --> 01:41:31.809
HARRY:
Ron. it's lying!

1067
01:41:31.984 --> 01:41:34.976
Your mother confessed
she would have preferred me as a son.

1068
01:41:35.154 --> 01:41:38.146
What woman would take you?

1069
01:41:38.357 --> 01:41:41.520
You are nothing.

1070
01:41:41.694 --> 01:41:42.820
Nothing.

1071
01:41:43.595 --> 01:41:47.622
Nothing compared to him.

1072
01:42:07.319 --> 01:42:08.547
[RON YELLS]

1073
01:42:11.824 --> 01:42:13.815
[PANTING]

1074
01:42:25.971 --> 01:42:27.962
[PANTING]

1075
01:42:38.183 --> 01:42:39.844
RON:
Just think...

1076
01:42:40.753 --> 01:42:42.846
...only three to go.

1077
01:42:45.891 --> 01:42:47.620
HARRY:
Hermione?

1078
01:42:49.895 --> 01:42:51.624
Hermione?

1079
01:42:56.168 --> 01:42:58.102
Is everything all right?

1080
01:42:58.737 --> 01:43:03.401
It's fine.
Actually. you know. it's more than fine.

1081
01:43:07.846 --> 01:43:09.438
Hey.

1082
01:43:13.685 --> 01:43:19.885
You complete ass. Ronald Weasley!

1083
01:43:20.058 --> 01:43:23.721
You show up here after weeks.
and you say "hey"?

1084
01:43:25.931 --> 01:43:28.661
- Where's my wand? Where's my wand?
- I don't know.

1085
01:43:28.834 --> 01:43:31.098
- Harry Potter. give me my wand.
- I don't have it.

1086
01:43:31.270 --> 01:43:35.104
- How come he's got your wand?
- Never mind why he's got my wand.

1087
01:43:37.376 --> 01:43:38.604
What is that?

1088
01:43:41.547 --> 01:43:42.571
You destroyed it.

1089
01:43:45.884 --> 01:43:49.843
And how is it that you just happen
to have the sword of Gryffindor?

1090
01:43:50.255 --> 01:43:52.223
It's a long story.

1091
01:43:55.394 --> 01:43:59.490
- Don't think this changes anything.
- Oh. of course not.

1092
01:43:59.665 --> 01:44:02.930
I only just destroyed a bloody Horcrux.
Why would that change anything?

1093
01:44:03.101 --> 01:44:07.162
Look. I wanted to come back
as soon as I left.

1094
01:44:07.339 --> 01:44:10.775
- I just didn't know how to find you.
HARRY: Yeah. how did you find us?

1095
01:44:10.943 --> 01:44:14.003
With this. It doesn't just turn off lights.

1096
01:44:14.179 --> 01:44:19.082
I don't know how it works. but Christmas
morning I was sleeping in this little pub...

1097
01:44:19.251 --> 01:44:21.685
...keeping away from some Snatchers...

1098
01:44:22.120 --> 01:44:23.382
...and I heard it.

1099
01:44:23.789 --> 01:44:25.222
It?

1100
01:44:26.558 --> 01:44:28.492
A voice...

1101
01:44:30.095 --> 01:44:31.289
...your voice. Hermione...

1102
01:44:32.464 --> 01:44:34.091
...coming out of it.

1103
01:44:34.266 --> 01:44:38.100
- And what exactly did I say. may I ask?
- My name.

1104
01:44:38.704 --> 01:44:40.729
Just my name.

1105
01:44:41.506 --> 01:44:43.599
Like a whisper.

1106
01:44:45.577 --> 01:44:51.573
So I took it. clicked it.
and this tiny ball of light appeared.

1107
01:44:52.050 --> 01:44:53.483
And I knew.

1108
01:44:54.052 --> 01:44:58.682
And sure enough. it floated toward me.
the ball of light...

1109
01:45:00.392 --> 01:45:04.590
...went right to my chest.
straight through me. Right here.

1110
01:45:05.797 --> 01:45:09.790
And I knew it was gonna take me
where I needed to go. so I Disapparated...

1111
01:45:09.968 --> 01:45:12.232
...and came to this hillside.

1112
01:45:12.771 --> 01:45:15.296
It was dark. I had no idea where I was.

1113
01:45:15.841 --> 01:45:18.674
I just hoped
that one of you would show yourself.

1114
01:45:19.578 --> 01:45:21.102
And you did.

1115
01:45:38.530 --> 01:45:41.431
I've always liked these flames
Hermione makes.

1116
01:45:45.470 --> 01:45:48.030
How long do you reckon
she'll stay mad at me?

1117
01:45:49.574 --> 01:45:52.907
Well. just keep talking about that
little ball of light touching your heart...

1118
01:45:53.078 --> 01:45:54.511
...and she�ll come round.

1119
01:45:54.680 --> 01:45:57.410
It was true. Every word.

1120
01:45:59.217 --> 01:46:01.583
This is gonna sound crazy...

1121
01:46:02.054 --> 01:46:06.423
...but I think that's why Dumbledore
left it to me. the Deluminator.

1122
01:46:06.925 --> 01:46:11.919
I think he knew that somehow I'd need it
to find my way back. and she'd lead me.

1123
01:46:14.800 --> 01:46:17.530
Bloody hell. I just realized.
you need a wand. don't you?

1124
01:46:17.703 --> 01:46:20.194
- Yeah.
- I've got one here.

1125
01:46:20.472 --> 01:46:23.066
It's a blackthorn. Ten inches.

1126
01:46:23.241 --> 01:46:26.836
Nothing special. but I reckon it�ll do.

1127
01:46:27.279 --> 01:46:30.077
Took if off a Snatcher
a couple of weeks ago.

1128
01:46:30.582 --> 01:46:34.416
Don't tell Hermione this.
but they're a bit dim. Snatchers.

1129
01:46:34.686 --> 01:46:37.621
This one was definitely part troll.
the smell of him.

1130
01:46:37.789 --> 01:46:38.813
<i>Engorgio.

1131
01:46:38.991 --> 01:46:41.152
<i>- Reducio!
HERMIONE: What's going on in there?

1132
01:46:41.326 --> 01:46:42.588
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

1133
01:46:44.963 --> 01:46:46.590
We need to talk.

1134
01:46:47.399 --> 01:46:48.593
Yeah. all right.

1135
01:46:55.574 --> 01:46:59.101
- I want to go see Xenophilius Lovegood.
- Sorry?

1136
01:47:00.879 --> 01:47:02.506
See this?

1137
01:47:02.681 --> 01:47:06.549
It's a letter Dumbledore wrote
to Grindelwald. Look at the signature.

1138
01:47:07.786 --> 01:47:09.981
It's the mark again.

1139
01:47:10.922 --> 01:47:13.049
It keeps cropping up.

1140
01:47:13.225 --> 01:47:17.594
<i>In Beedle the Bard.
in the graveyard in Godric's Hollow.

1141
01:47:18.430 --> 01:47:20.295
HARRY:
It was there too.

1142
01:47:20.465 --> 01:47:24.060
- Where?
HARRY: Outside Gregorovitch's Wand Shop.

1143
01:47:24.503 --> 01:47:25.731
But what does it mean?

1144
01:47:25.904 --> 01:47:30.705
Look. you've got no idea where
the next Horcrux is. and neither do I...

1145
01:47:32.411 --> 01:47:35.346
...but this. this means something.

1146
01:47:35.680 --> 01:47:39.081
- I'm sure of it.
- Yeah. Hermione's right.

1147
01:47:40.118 --> 01:47:42.211
We ought to see Lovegood.

1148
01:47:42.721 --> 01:47:46.452
Let's vote on it. Those in favor?

1149
01:48:10.282 --> 01:48:12.910
You're not still mad at him. are you?

1150
01:48:13.218 --> 01:48:15.482
I'm always mad at him.

1151
01:48:18.256 --> 01:48:19.746
RON:
Luna.

1152
01:48:19.925 --> 01:48:21.620
HERMIONE & HARRY:
Luna.

1153
01:48:28.100 --> 01:48:29.124
[KNOCKING]

1154
01:48:29.301 --> 01:48:32.134
"Keep off the dirigible plums. "

1155
01:48:41.179 --> 01:48:43.875
What is it? Who are you?

1156
01:48:44.182 --> 01:48:45.206
What do you want?

1157
01:48:45.383 --> 01:48:49.979
Hello. Mr. Lovegood. I'm Harry Potter.
We met a few months ago.

1158
01:48:53.992 --> 01:48:55.892
Could we come in?

1159
01:48:59.664 --> 01:49:02.258
HERMIONE: Where is Luna?
- Luna?

1160
01:49:03.535 --> 01:49:05.503
She'll be along.

1161
01:49:19.017 --> 01:49:21.076
So how can I help you. Mr. Potter?

1162
01:49:21.920 --> 01:49:24.946
Well. actually...

1163
01:49:25.957 --> 01:49:30.485
It was about something you were wearing
round your neck at the wedding. A symbol.

1164
01:49:32.030 --> 01:49:33.930
You mean this?

1165
01:49:34.332 --> 01:49:35.924
Yes.

1166
01:49:36.234 --> 01:49:38.099
That exactly.

1167
01:49:38.770 --> 01:49:42.729
What we've wondered is. what is it?

1168
01:49:42.908 --> 01:49:44.739
What is it?

1169
01:49:44.910 --> 01:49:47.879
Well. it's the sign of the Deathly Hallows.
of course.

1170
01:49:48.046 --> 01:49:49.138
RON & HERMIONE: The what?
- The what?

1171
01:49:49.314 --> 01:49:51.373
The Deathly Hallows.

1172
01:49:51.550 --> 01:49:54.644
I assume you're all familiar with
"The Tale of the Three Brothers. "

1173
01:49:54.819 --> 01:49:56.309
RON & HERMIONE: Yes.
- No.

1174
01:50:01.660 --> 01:50:03.423
HERMIONE:
I have it in here.

1175
01:50:14.673 --> 01:50:16.300
"There were once three brothers...

1176
01:50:16.474 --> 01:50:20.877
...who were traveling along a lonely.
winding road at twilight. "

1177
01:50:21.046 --> 01:50:23.776
Midnight. Mom always said "midnight. "

1178
01:50:28.787 --> 01:50:32.655
But "twilight�s" fine. Better. actually.

1179
01:50:34.926 --> 01:50:36.791
HERMIONE:
Do you want to read it?

1180
01:50:36.962 --> 01:50:39.157
RON:
No. It's fine.

1181
01:50:41.066 --> 01:50:43.000
<i>HERMIONE:
"There were once three brothers...

1182
01:50:43.168 --> 01:50:48.367
<i>...who were traveling along a lonely.
winding road at twilight.

1183
01:50:50.242 --> 01:50:55.544
<i>In time. the brothers reached a river
too treacherous to pass.

1184
01:50:55.880 --> 01:50:57.745
<i>But being learned in the magical arts...

1185
01:50:57.916 --> 01:51:03.081
<i>...the three brothers simply
waved their wands and made a bridge.

1186
01:51:04.422 --> 01:51:06.515
<i>Before they could cross. however...

1187
01:51:06.691 --> 01:51:10.787
<i>...they found their path blocked
by a hooded figure.

1188
01:51:11.062 --> 01:51:14.930
<i>It was Death. and he felt cheated.

1189
01:51:15.100 --> 01:51:18.160
<i>Cheated because travelers would
normally drown in the river.

1190
01:51:18.336 --> 01:51:20.395
<i>But Death was cunning.

1191
01:51:21.039 --> 01:51:24.031
<i>He pretended to congratulate
the three brothers on their magic...

1192
01:51:24.209 --> 01:51:29.476
<i>...and said that each had earned a prize for
having been clever enough to evade him.

1193
01:51:30.048 --> 01:51:34.610
<i>The oldest asked for a wand
more powerful than any in existence.

1194
01:51:34.786 --> 01:51:39.382
<i>So Death fashioned him one
from an elder tree that stood nearby.

1195
01:51:40.792 --> 01:51:45.092
<i>The second brother decided he wanted
to humiliate Death even further...

1196
01:51:45.263 --> 01:51:49.700
<i>...and asked for the power
to recall loved ones from the grave.

1197
01:51:50.135 --> 01:51:54.435
<i>So Death plucked a stone from the river
and offered it to him.

1198
01:51:55.173 --> 01:51:59.132
<i>Finally.
Death turned to the third brother.

1199
01:52:00.345 --> 01:52:01.778
<i>A humble man...

1200
01:52:01.946 --> 01:52:06.144
<i>...he asked for something that would
allow him to go forth from that place...

1201
01:52:06.318 --> 01:52:09.481
<i>...without being followed by Death.

1202
01:52:10.588 --> 01:52:16.458
<i>And so it was that Death reluctantly
handed over his own Cloak of Invisibility.

1203
01:52:19.831 --> 01:52:22.766
<i>The first brother traveled
to a distant village...

1204
01:52:22.934 --> 01:52:25.027
<i>...where. with the Elder Wand in hand...

1205
01:52:25.203 --> 01:52:28.969
<i>...he killed a wizard
with whom he had once quarreled.

1206
01:52:31.176 --> 01:52:34.703
<i>Drunk with the power
that the Elder Wand had given him...

1207
01:52:34.879 --> 01:52:37.973
<i>...he bragged of his invincibility.

1208
01:52:40.985 --> 01:52:44.443
<i>But that night.
another wizard stole the wand...

1209
01:52:44.622 --> 01:52:47.750
<i>...and slit the brother's throat
for good measure.

1210
01:52:47.959 --> 01:52:51.395
<i>And so Death took the first brother
for his own.

1211
01:52:52.130 --> 01:52:54.098
<i>The second brother journeyed
to his home...

1212
01:52:54.265 --> 01:52:57.234
<i>...where he took the stone
and turned it thrice in hand.

1213
01:52:57.402 --> 01:53:01.862
<i>To his delight. the girl he'd once hoped
to marry before her untimely death...

1214
01:53:02.040 --> 01:53:04.406
<i>...appeared before him.

1215
01:53:04.909 --> 01:53:10.211
<i>Yet. soon she turned sad and cold
for she did not belong in the mortal world.

1216
01:53:10.382 --> 01:53:12.009
<i>Driven mad with hopeless longing...

1217
01:53:12.183 --> 01:53:15.482
<i>...the second brother killed himself
so as to join her.

1218
01:53:16.688 --> 01:53:19.782
<i>And so Death took the second brother.

1219
01:53:19.958 --> 01:53:21.585
<i>As for the third brother...

1220
01:53:21.760 --> 01:53:25.992
<i>...Death searched for many years
but was never able to find him.

1221
01:53:26.164 --> 01:53:29.065
<i>Only when he attained a great age
did the youngest brother...

1222
01:53:29.234 --> 01:53:33.500
<i>...shed the Cloak of Invisibility
and give it to his son.

1223
01:53:34.739 --> 01:53:38.869
<i>He then greeted Death as an old friend
and went with him gladly...

1224
01:53:39.043 --> 01:53:42.206
<i>...departing this life as equals. "

1225
01:53:42.380 --> 01:53:44.109
[SQUAWKING]

1226
01:53:44.282 --> 01:53:48.776
XENOPHILIUS: So there you are.
Those are the Deathly Hallows.

1227
01:53:50.188 --> 01:53:53.248
I'm sorry. sir.
I still don't quite understand.

1228
01:53:55.493 --> 01:53:57.825
[MUMBLING]

1229
01:53:58.863 --> 01:54:00.956
Where's that pen I had?

1230
01:54:11.943 --> 01:54:13.205
The Eider Wand.

1231
01:54:14.345 --> 01:54:18.008
The most powerful wand ever made.

1232
01:54:28.393 --> 01:54:30.691
The Resurrection Stone.

1233
01:54:41.573 --> 01:54:45.339
The Cloak of Invisibility.

1234
01:54:47.378 --> 01:54:50.506
Together. they make the Deathly Hallows.

1235
01:54:50.782 --> 01:54:56.243
Together. they make one
master of Death.

1236
01:55:01.459 --> 01:55:05.122
That mark was on a grave
in Godric's Hollow.

1237
01:55:06.231 --> 01:55:08.859
Uh. Mr. Lovegood.
does the Peverell Family...

1238
01:55:09.033 --> 01:55:10.864
...have anything to do
with the Deathly Hallows?

1239
01:55:11.035 --> 01:55:13.868
Uh- Uh-

1240
01:55:14.038 --> 01:55:17.804
Ignotus- Excuse me. -and his brothers.
Cadmus and Antioch...

1241
01:55:17.976 --> 01:55:20.638
...are thought to be the original owners
of the Hallows...

1242
01:55:20.812 --> 01:55:25.681
...and therefore the inspiration
for the story. Uh- Uh-

1243
01:55:25.850 --> 01:55:28.341
But your tea's gone cold.

1244
01:55:29.554 --> 01:55:31.545
I'll be right back.

1245
01:55:31.723 --> 01:55:33.588
Let's go down here.

1246
01:55:35.460 --> 01:55:36.950
Let's get out of here.

1247
01:55:37.128 --> 01:55:39.995
I'm not drinking any more of that stuff.
hot or cold.

1248
01:55:46.304 --> 01:55:48.272
Thank you. sir.

1249
01:55:49.173 --> 01:55:52.199
- You forgot the water.
- Water?

1250
01:55:52.377 --> 01:55:53.810
For the tea.

1251
01:55:53.978 --> 01:55:56.538
Did-? Did I?

1252
01:55:56.714 --> 01:55:58.306
[XENOPHILIUS LAUGHING]

1253
01:55:58.483 --> 01:56:00.644
How silly of me.

1254
01:56:02.253 --> 01:56:04.517
It's no matter.
We really should be going anyway.

1255
01:56:04.689 --> 01:56:06.748
No. you can't!

1256
01:56:06.925 --> 01:56:08.415
[MUMBLING]

1257
01:56:10.962 --> 01:56:12.657
HARRY:
Sir?

1258
01:56:20.038 --> 01:56:22.632
You're my only hope.

1259
01:56:26.511 --> 01:56:30.880
They were angry. you see.
about what I'd been writing.

1260
01:56:33.918 --> 01:56:36.045
So they took her.

1261
01:56:37.522 --> 01:56:40.286
They took my Luna.

1262
01:56:41.993 --> 01:56:43.620
My Luna.

1263
01:56:56.107 --> 01:56:59.008
But it's really you they want.

1264
01:57:01.245 --> 01:57:03.304
Who took her. sir?

1265
01:57:08.453 --> 01:57:09.715
Voldemort.

1266
01:57:12.256 --> 01:57:13.280
[SHRIEKING]

1267
01:57:13.458 --> 01:57:15.153
[HERMIONE SHRIEKS]

1268
01:57:20.365 --> 01:57:22.663
Stop! I've got him!

1269
01:57:27.905 --> 01:57:28.929
[GROANS]

1270
01:57:39.951 --> 01:57:43.853
That treacherous little bleeder.
Is there no one we can trust?

1271
01:57:44.022 --> 01:57:46.320
They kidnapped her
because he supported me.

1272
01:57:46.491 --> 01:57:48.618
He was just desperate.

1273
01:57:49.160 --> 01:57:51.355
I'll do the enchantments.

1274
01:58:03.041 --> 01:58:04.474
Hello. beautiful.

1275
01:58:09.947 --> 01:58:13.576
Well. don't hang about. snatch them.

1276
01:58:18.189 --> 01:58:20.623
[ALL PANTING]

1277
01:58:26.564 --> 01:58:28.088
[HERMIONE YELLS]

1278
01:58:33.971 --> 01:58:34.995
[GRUNTS]

1279
01:58:49.020 --> 01:58:50.578
[GRUNTING]

1280
01:59:23.154 --> 01:59:24.644
[GROANS]

1281
01:59:24.822 --> 01:59:26.312
<i>VOLDEMORT:
Harry.

1282
01:59:26.491 --> 01:59:29.460
<i>Tell me. Grindelwald.
Tell me where it is.

1283
01:59:30.061 --> 01:59:34.122
<i>Grindelwald. Grindelwald. Grindelwald.

1284
01:59:34.866 --> 01:59:38.324
Hello. Tom.
I knew you would come one day...

1285
01:59:38.803 --> 01:59:42.762
...but surely you must know
I no longer have what you seek.

1286
01:59:43.407 --> 01:59:46.433
- Tell me. Grindelwald. Tell me where it is.
- Ha-ha-ha.

1287
01:59:46.611 --> 01:59:47.976
Tell me who possesses it.

1288
01:59:48.179 --> 01:59:53.276
The Eider Wand lies with him.
of course...

1289
01:59:53.451 --> 01:59:55.715
...buried in the earth.

1290
01:59:56.654 --> 01:59:57.985
Dumbledore.

1291
02:00:02.226 --> 02:00:04.217
[PANTING THEN SIGHS]

1292
02:00:07.031 --> 02:00:08.896
HARRY:
The Hallows exist...

1293
02:00:09.066 --> 02:00:12.866
...but he's only after one of them.
the last one. He knows where it is.

1294
02:00:13.037 --> 02:00:16.871
He's gonna have it by the end of the night.
You-Know-Who's found the Eider Wand.

1295
02:00:17.041 --> 02:00:19.509
- Don't touch her. Unh!
HERMIONE: Leave him.

1296
02:00:19.677 --> 02:00:20.939
SCABIOR:
Your boyfriend will get worse than that...

1297
02:00:21.112 --> 02:00:22.238
Get off me.

1298
02:00:22.413 --> 02:00:25.143
...if he doesn't learn to behave himself.

1299
02:00:25.316 --> 02:00:27.307
[HARRY & RON GRUNTING]

1300
02:00:28.386 --> 02:00:29.876
What happened to you. ugly?

1301
02:00:31.589 --> 02:00:33.454
No. not you.

1302
02:00:34.859 --> 02:00:37.919
- What's your name?
- Dudley. Vernon Dudley.

1303
02:00:38.095 --> 02:00:40.290
SCABIOR:
Check it.

1304
02:00:40.464 --> 02:00:41.726
[HERMIONE GRUNTING]

1305
02:00:41.899 --> 02:00:44.231
And you. my lovely...

1306
02:00:47.538 --> 02:00:49.529
...what do they call you?

1307
02:00:50.975 --> 02:00:55.036
Penelope Clearwater. half-blood.

1308
02:00:56.948 --> 02:00:57.972
[SNIFFS]

1309
02:00:58.149 --> 02:01:00.083
There's no Vernon Dudley on here.

1310
02:01:01.152 --> 02:01:04.383
GREYBACK: Did you hear that. ugly?
The list says you're lying.

1311
02:01:04.555 --> 02:01:06.785
How come you don't want us
to know who you are?

1312
02:01:06.958 --> 02:01:09.620
The list's wrong. I told you who I am.

1313
02:01:25.576 --> 02:01:27.669
Change of plan.

1314
02:01:28.746 --> 02:01:32.011
We're not taking this lot to the Ministry.

1315
02:02:11.689 --> 02:02:15.318
BELLATRIX [WHISPERS]:
Get Draco.

1316
02:02:16.427 --> 02:02:18.418
[GRUNTS AND PANTS]

1317
02:02:19.797 --> 02:02:21.355
BELLATRIX:
Well?

1318
02:02:24.468 --> 02:02:28.996
DRACO: I can't be sure.
- [WHISPERS] Draco. Look closely. son.

1319
02:02:30.007 --> 02:02:35.070
If we are the ones
to hand Potter over to the Dark Lord...

1320
02:02:35.246 --> 02:02:40.479
...everything would be forgiven.
All would be as it was. you understand?

1321
02:02:40.651 --> 02:02:44.781
Now. we won't be forgetting who
actually caught him. I hope. Mr. Malfoy.

1322
02:02:44.956 --> 02:02:47.390
[IN NORMAL VOICE] You dare to
talk to me like that in my own house?

1323
02:02:47.558 --> 02:02:49.355
Lucius.

1324
02:02:52.263 --> 02:02:56.097
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Don't be shy. sweetie. Come over.

1325
02:02:57.601 --> 02:03:02.368
Now. if this isn't who we think it is. Draco.
and we call him. he�ll kill us all.

1326
02:03:02.540 --> 02:03:05.338
We need to be absolutely sure.

1327
02:03:05.643 --> 02:03:06.632
What's wrong with his face?

1328
02:03:06.811 --> 02:03:08.540
BELLATRIX:
Yes. what is wrong with his face?

1329
02:03:08.713 --> 02:03:09.907
SCABIOR:
He came to us like that.

1330
02:03:10.081 --> 02:03:12.049
Something he picked up in the forest.
I reckon.

1331
02:03:12.216 --> 02:03:15.913
Or ran into a Stinging Jinx.
Was it you. dearie?

1332
02:03:21.025 --> 02:03:23.789
Give me her wand.
We�ll see what her last spell was.

1333
02:03:25.062 --> 02:03:27.223
Ah. Got you.

1334
02:03:27.398 --> 02:03:29.389
[LAUGHING THEN GASPS]

1335
02:03:31.035 --> 02:03:32.764
What is that?

1336
02:03:34.705 --> 02:03:36.297
Where'd you get that from?

1337
02:03:36.474 --> 02:03:39.966
It was in her bag when we searched her.
Reckon it's mine now.

1338
02:03:40.745 --> 02:03:42.212
[BELLATRIX GRUNTING]

1339
02:03:42.380 --> 02:03:43.540
[HISSES]

1340
02:03:43.714 --> 02:03:45.045
SCABIOR:
Are you mad?

1341
02:03:45.216 --> 02:03:46.877
[GROANING AND CHOKING]

1342
02:03:53.357 --> 02:03:56.190
Go! Get out!

1343
02:04:01.832 --> 02:04:05.996
Cissy. put the boys in the cellar.

1344
02:04:06.170 --> 02:04:11.540
I want to have a little conversation
with this one. girl-to-girl.

1345
02:04:13.711 --> 02:04:15.702
[BOTH GRUNT]

1346
02:04:15.880 --> 02:04:17.313
[DOOR CLOSES]

1347
02:04:20.584 --> 02:04:23.678
What are we gonna do?
We can't leave Hermione alone with her.

1348
02:04:23.854 --> 02:04:25.219
GIRL:
Ron?

1349
02:04:30.428 --> 02:04:31.986
Harry?

1350
02:04:37.701 --> 02:04:39.259
Luna?

1351
02:04:39.870 --> 02:04:44.034
That sword is meant to be in my vault
at Gringotts. How did you get it?

1352
02:04:44.208 --> 02:04:47.336
What else did you and your friends take
from my vault?!

1353
02:04:47.511 --> 02:04:52.881
[SOBBING] I didn't take anything. Please.
I didn't take anything.

1354
02:04:53.050 --> 02:04:54.574
I don't believe it.

1355
02:04:54.752 --> 02:04:55.980
[SCREAMING]

1356
02:04:56.153 --> 02:04:57.450
[BELLATRIX LAUGHS]

1357
02:05:00.157 --> 02:05:01.249
We have to do something.

1358
02:05:01.425 --> 02:05:05.452
There's no way out of here.
We've tried everything. It's enchanted.

1359
02:05:05.629 --> 02:05:08.325
HERMIONE: Please! please!
BELLATRIX: Shut up!

1360
02:05:08.499 --> 02:05:10.296
LUNA:
You're bleeding. Harry.

1361
02:05:10.468 --> 02:05:12.493
That's a curious thing
to keep in your sock.

1362
02:05:14.805 --> 02:05:16.796
[HERMIONE CONTINUES SCREAMING]

1363
02:05:21.745 --> 02:05:22.871
Help us.

1364
02:05:28.652 --> 02:05:30.552
- Let her go.
WORMTAIL: Shut up. Get back.

1365
02:05:31.889 --> 02:05:36.087
You. goblin. come with me.

1366
02:05:52.710 --> 02:05:54.701
[DOBBY GRUNTS]

1367
02:05:55.746 --> 02:05:57.236
- Aah!
- Dobby?

1368
02:05:58.115 --> 02:05:59.514
What are you doing here?

1369
02:05:59.683 --> 02:06:01.947
Dobby has come to rescue
Harry Potter. of course.

1370
02:06:02.119 --> 02:06:04.587
Dobby will always be there
for Harry Potter.

1371
02:06:04.755 --> 02:06:08.350
You can Apparate in and out of this room?
Could you take us with you?

1372
02:06:08.526 --> 02:06:10.289
Of course. sir. I'm an elf.

1373
02:06:11.095 --> 02:06:12.960
Works for me.

1374
02:06:13.197 --> 02:06:15.563
Dobby. I want you to take Luna
and Mr. Ollivander-

1375
02:06:15.733 --> 02:06:18.167
Shell Cottage
on the outskirts of Tinworth.

1376
02:06:18.536 --> 02:06:19.560
Trust me.

1377
02:06:20.371 --> 02:06:21.804
Whenever you're ready. sir.

1378
02:06:22.506 --> 02:06:25.202
Sir? I like her very much.

1379
02:06:26.243 --> 02:06:28.234
[DOBBY MUMBLING]

1380
02:06:30.147 --> 02:06:33.446
Meet me at the top of the stairs
in 10 seconds.

1381
02:06:40.424 --> 02:06:42.221
[GRUNTS]

1382
02:06:42.526 --> 02:06:44.289
Ow.

1383
02:06:49.700 --> 02:06:51.930
Who gets his wand?

1384
02:06:54.672 --> 02:06:58.665
BELLATRIX: I'm only going to
ask you once more. goblin.

1385
02:06:58.842 --> 02:07:02.243
Think very. very carefully
before you answer.

1386
02:07:02.613 --> 02:07:04.171
GRIPHOOK:
I don't know.

1387
02:07:04.348 --> 02:07:07.545
You don't know?
Why weren't you doing your job?

1388
02:07:07.718 --> 02:07:10.949
Who got into my vault?

1389
02:07:12.223 --> 02:07:16.660
Who stole it? Who stole it? Well?

1390
02:07:16.827 --> 02:07:20.854
GRIPHOOK: When I was last in your vault.
the sword was there.

1391
02:07:23.634 --> 02:07:26.831
BELLATRIX: Oh. well then. perhaps
it just walked out on its own then.

1392
02:07:27.004 --> 02:07:29.438
GRIPHOOK:
There is no place safer than Gringotts.

1393
02:07:29.607 --> 02:07:31.040
Liar!

1394
02:07:32.977 --> 02:07:36.378
Consider yourself lucky. goblin.

1395
02:07:38.816 --> 02:07:42.217
The same won't be said for this one.

1396
02:07:42.386 --> 02:07:44.149
Like hell.

1397
02:07:44.888 --> 02:07:46.116
<i>Expellliarmus!

1398
02:07:47.558 --> 02:07:48.650
<i>Stupefy.

1399
02:07:52.796 --> 02:07:54.161
BELLATRIX:
Stop!

1400
02:07:55.332 --> 02:07:56.890
Drop your wands.

1401
02:07:59.770 --> 02:08:00.794
I said. drop them!

1402
02:08:02.306 --> 02:08:03.739
Pick them up. Draco. now.

1403
02:08:04.608 --> 02:08:08.738
Well. well. well.
look what we have here.

1404
02:08:10.347 --> 02:08:11.837
It's Harry Potter.

1405
02:08:12.616 --> 02:08:18.987
He's all bright and shiny and new again.
just in time for the Dark Lord.

1406
02:08:19.156 --> 02:08:21.181
Call him.

1407
02:08:24.928 --> 02:08:26.725
Call him.

1408
02:08:41.211 --> 02:08:43.202
[SQUEAKING]

1409
02:08:52.756 --> 02:08:54.189
[BELLATRIX YELLS]

1410
02:08:57.194 --> 02:08:59.185
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1411
02:09:01.932 --> 02:09:03.763
<i>Stupefy!

1412
02:09:04.535 --> 02:09:06.230
BELLATRIX:
Stupid elf.

1413
02:09:06.403 --> 02:09:09.429
- You could�ve killed me.
- Dobby never meant to kill.

1414
02:09:09.606 --> 02:09:13.633
Dobby only meant to maim
or seriously injure.

1415
02:09:14.745 --> 02:09:15.769
[NARCISSA GRUNTS]

1416
02:09:15.946 --> 02:09:19.279
How dare you take a witch's wand?

1417
02:09:19.450 --> 02:09:22.442
How dare you defy your masters?

1418
02:09:22.619 --> 02:09:25.747
Dobby has no master.

1419
02:09:25.923 --> 02:09:28.414
Dobby is a free elf.

1420
02:09:28.592 --> 02:09:33.552
And Dobby has come
to save Harry Potter and his friends.

1421
02:09:50.881 --> 02:09:52.508
[WHOOSH]

1422
02:09:53.650 --> 02:09:55.641
[HARRY PANTING]

1423
02:10:03.394 --> 02:10:05.055
Hermione.

1424
02:10:05.229 --> 02:10:07.720
You're all right. We're safe.

1425
02:10:07.898 --> 02:10:09.923
We're all safe.

1426
02:10:10.801 --> 02:10:12.996
DOBBY:
Harry Potter.

1427
02:10:16.740 --> 02:10:18.571
Dobby.

1428
02:10:24.281 --> 02:10:26.272
[DOBBY GROANS]

1429
02:10:29.086 --> 02:10:32.146
Dobby. No. just- Hold on.

1430
02:10:32.322 --> 02:10:36.656
Hold on. Look. just hold on. okay?

1431
02:10:36.827 --> 02:10:38.886
We�ll fix you.

1432
02:10:39.329 --> 02:10:42.059
Hermione will have something.

1433
02:10:42.232 --> 02:10:44.564
In your bag. Hermione?

1434
02:10:46.203 --> 02:10:47.534
Hermione?

1435
02:10:49.740 --> 02:10:52.868
What is it? Help me.

1436
02:10:55.446 --> 02:10:58.574
Such a beautiful place...

1437
02:11:00.751 --> 02:11:03.015
...to be with friends.

1438
02:11:04.822 --> 02:11:10.226
Dobby is happy to be with his friend...

1439
02:11:12.629 --> 02:11:15.063
...Harry Potter.

1440
02:11:35.853 --> 02:11:38.253
We should close his eyes.

1441
02:11:38.489 --> 02:11:40.514
Don't you think?

1442
02:11:45.629 --> 02:11:47.028
There.

1443
02:11:47.498 --> 02:11:49.932
